data.subject: Embryo (From `Picnic`)
data.lyric:
All this love, is all I am
 A ball is all I am
 I'm so new compared with you
 And I am very small

data.subject: See Emily Play (Live In Stockholm 1967)
data.lyric:
Emily tries but misunderstands, ah ooh
 She often inclined to borrow somebody's dreams till tomorrow

data.subject: Set The Controls For The Heart Of The Sun (Live In Stockholm 1967)
data.lyric:
Little by little the night turns around
 Counting the leaves which tremble at dawn
 Lotuses lean on

data.subject: Scream Thy Last Scream (Live In Stockholm 1967)
data.lyric:
Scream thy last scream old woman with a casket
 Blam blam your pointers point your pointers
 Waddle

data.subject: Matilda Mother (Live In Stockholm 1967)
data.lyric:
There was a king who ruled the land
 His Majesty was in command
 With silver eyes the scarlet eagle

data.subject: Reaction In G (Live In Stockholm 1967)
data.lyric:
Deep in the ocean, dead and cast away
 Where innocence is burned in flames
 A million mile from home
